UNICEF aims to achieve this through Data, Research, Evaluation And Knowledge Management, Evaluations, Research And Data, Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Innovation, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2023, National institutions and local authorities enable the population, especially the most vulnerable, to exercise their rights with regard to health, nutrition, and access to water and sanitation, in order to realise the democratic dividend and achieve the SDGs

title.narrative: New Element

description.narrative: UNICEF’s programme and field coordination functions were very active in 2021, with a doubled budget, a L2 emergency response, and the opening of 3 field offices in the south. Field-based Programme Officers are seeing improved coordination as a result of the field office structure. The bigger budget meant more activities to coordinate in terms of partnerships with NGOs; financial assurance activities, field monitoring, and quality control. Also training on prevention and response to PSEA for 300 stakeholders was provided, and 3 evaluations completed.;UNICEF also prepared, submitted and implemented a new CPD in 2021. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:24/12/2021
